HEADWORD: Innervate
<hw>In*ner"vate</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*n⟦etil⟧r"v⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Innerve</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>To
supply with nerves; <as>as, the heart is <ex>innervated</ex> by
pneumogastric and sympathetic branches</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

